.TH NYANNYAN 1 "June 2026" "1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nyannyan \- display a sleeping cat ASCII art animation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nyannyan
[\fI\-t seconds\fR]
[\fI\-wakeup\fR]
[\fI\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnyannyan\fR is a joke command that displays a sleeping cat ASCII art animation in the terminal.
By default, it shows the animation for 3 seconds and then returns to the normal terminal.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t " " \fIseconds\fR
Specify the duration of the animation in seconds. If 0, the animation runs infinitely until interrupted (e.g., via Ctrl+C). Default is 3.
.TP
.B \-wakeup
Display a sequence where the sleeping cat wakes up, stretches, and stands up.
.TP
.B \-help ", " \-\-help
Display a help message and exit.
